							<div class="post_wrapper author">
								<div id="about_the_author">
									<div class="gravatar"><a href="https://lithub.com/author/kristineservin/"><img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/Kristine-S.-Ervin-100x100.jpg" width="100" height="100" alt="Kristine S. Ervin" class="avatar avatar-100 wp-user-avatar wp-user-avatar-100 alignnone photo" /></a></div>
									<div class="description author withsidebar">
										<h6><a href="https://lithub.com/author/kristineservin/">Kristine S. Ervin</a></h6>
										Kristine S. Ervin grew up in a small suburb of Oklahoma City and now teaches creative writing at West Chester University, outside Philadelphia. She holds an MFA in poetry from New York University and a PhD in creative writing and literature, with a focus in nonfiction, from the University of Houston.																			</div>
